claim.claim-text:
An endoscope system (10) comprising:
a lighting means (13, 43, 48, 22) for applying special illumination light to a body portion, said special illumination light having a wavelength at which oxyhemoglobin and deoxyhemoglobin have different absorption coefficients;
an imaging means (47, 49) having a normal image sensor (53) and a high-sensitivity image sensor (60), for capturing an image of said body portion irradiated with said special illumination light;
a light amount measurement means (78) for measuring a reflected light amount of said special illumination light based on a signal obtained by said imaging means (47, 49);
an imaging control means (70) for changing operating conditions of said normal and high-sensitivity image sensors (53, 60) in accordance with said reflected light amount; and
a special image processing means (80) for producing a special image (91) depicting an oxygen saturation level of blood based on said signal obtained by said imaging means (47, 49) under control of said imaging control means (70).

A method for controlling an endoscope system (10), said endoscope system (10) including a lighting means (13, 43, 48, 22) for applying to a body portion special illumination light having a wavelength at which oxyhemoglobin and deoxyhemoglobin have different absorption coefficients, and an imaging means (47, 49) having a normal image sensor (53) and a high-sensitivity image sensor (60), said method comprising the steps of:
applying said special illumination light to said body portion;
guiding said special illumination light reflected from said body portion to said imaging means (47, 49);
measuring a reflected light amount of said special illumination light based on a signal obtained by said imaging means (47, 49);
changing operating conditions of said normal and high-sensitivity image sensors (53, 60) in accordance with said measured reflected light amount;
operating said normal and high-sensitivity image sensors (53, 60) in said changed operating conditions, and imaging said body portion under irradiation with said special illumination light; and
producing a special image (91) depicting an oxygen saturation level of blood based on an image signal obtained by said normal or high-sensitivity image sensor (53, 60).
